  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We investigate the running cosmological constant model with dark energy linearly proportional to the Hubble parameter, <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>σ</mi><mi>H</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math> , in which the <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi><mtext>CDM</mtext></math> limit is recovered by taking <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>σ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> . We derive the linear perturbation equations of gravity under the Friedmann–Lemaïtre–Robertson–Walker cosmology, and show the power spectra of the CMB temperature and matter density distribution. By using the Markov chain Monte Carlo method, we fit the model to the current observational data and find that <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>σ</mi><msub><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>≲</mo><mn>2.63</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> and <math altimg="si5.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>6.74</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> for <math altimg="si6.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> coupled to matter and radiation-matter, respectively, along with constraints on other cosmological parameters.</subfield>
